2 2025 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 6-126.2), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 6-126.2. A. An operator of a commercial motor vehicle
5 within this state shall be able to demonstrate proficiency of the
6 English language sufficient to:
7 1. Converse with the general public;
8 2. Understand highway traffic signs and signals in the English
9 language;
10 3. Respond to official inquiries; and
11 4. Make entries on reports and records.
12 When enforcing the provisions of this section, peace officers
13 may reference and apply applicable enforcement standards reflected
14 in Policy MC-SEE-2025-0001 issued by the Federal Motor Carrier
15 Safety Administration on May 20, 2025.
16 B. 1. A commercial motor carrier whose driver is found to be
17 in violation of this section shall be subject to a fine in the
18 amount of Three Thousand Dollars ($3,000.00) for each violation.
19 The proceeds of any penalties collected pursuant to this paragraph
20 shall be deposited in the Weigh Station Improvement Revolving Fund
21 created in Section 1167 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
22 2. A driver found to be in violation of this section shall be
23 prohibited from operating a commercial motor vehicle within this
24 state until such a time that the driver is able to meet the
Req. No. 3737 Page 23

1 iden tification provisions of this section. Any driver found to be
2 operating a motor vehicle within this state while under such
3 prohibition shall be guilty of a misdemeanor and upon conviction
4 shall be punished by a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars
5 ($1,000.00), or by imprisonment for not more than ninety (90) days,
6 or both such fine and imprisonment. Any fine collected pursuant to
7 the provisions of this paragraph shall be deposited to the Trauma
8 Care Assistance Revolving Fund created in Section 1-2530.9 of Title
9 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
10 3. The commercial motor carrier shall be notified of the
11 location of any commercial motor vehicle involved in a violation,
12 and, upon payment of the fine in full and presentation of a driver
13 who meets all requirements to operate a commercial motor vehicle
14 within this state, shall take possession of the vehicle. If the
